description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in the Hastings Assessment and Treatment Service for a part time Band 2 Clinical support worker to join our friendly, supportive and caring team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be a key part of our multi-disciplinary service for adults with mental health problems. This is challenging work but we receive very positive feedback from our service users and carers and Sussex Partnership NHS Foundation Trust has recently achieved Outstanding for the care it provides.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will include a range of clinical and non-clinical duties, focused mainly on improving the physical health of people with enduring mental illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will have strong communication and people skills, a non-judgmental and person-centred approach and above all a caring and compassionate attitude, valuing mental health equally with physical health and. with a commitment to improving the lives of our service users through creative, evidence based practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for working collaboratively with service users and their carers in order to meet their needs and maximise their independence.. You will also need to be able to work cohesively with other services both within our Trust, and with other partner agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to hold or work towards completing The Care Certificate, be able to record service user data onto our clinical system (training given) and work well within a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be keen to embrace new ways of working and enthusiastic about improving clinical practice in line with the latest research and organisational learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work across the Hastings and Rother area. Although the job specification cites the hours as ranging from 9am – 8pm, these posts are currently 9am – 5pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All our staff are given opportunities to develop and grow as professionals in the organisation. We provide regular supervision, a supportive working environment and access to training opportunities to assist you to realise your potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The town is right by the sea, and the office has amazing sea views, with the prom across the road. Art, theatre, poetry, writing and music are a large part of the town’s culture. It is a vibrant and quirky area, with some beautiful countryside around the more deprived urban areas. There is the acclaimed Jerwood Gallery next to a working fishing beach; an old town; castle; pier and of course the Guinness world record for the largest gathering of pirates is held by Hastings!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job share or part time working applications will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust offers the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent starting salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension contributions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days holiday allowance plus bank holidays (full time working equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Working patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Child care vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent training and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;john.allsopp@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01424 726553&lt;/p&gt;
